Homeland, a popular US television drama, based its fourth season in Islamabad, Pakistan.[80]
Last Resort was an American military drama television series was based on Pakistan.

Madam Secretary's first season's episode three was based on a diplomatic crises with Pakistan.
Pakistan Independence Day Parade: The event is held every year around August 14 (the date Pakistan was established in 1947) in New York City

APPNA Conference: This event is organized every year by APPNA (Association of Pakistani Physicians in North America).  The conference attracts hundreds of Pakistani American physicians and their families from all over North America. APPNA's doctors have also volunteered their time and services for a free health care event taking place throughout June 2010.[82]
